<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Maple Leafs 3, Oilers 2, OT  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    EDMONTON, Alberta (AP) -- Mats Sundin scored at 2:59 of overtime as the
Toronto Maple Leafs rallied from two goals down to beat the Edmonton Oilers 3-2
Friday night.
</P>
<P>
	   Sundin snapped a shot past goaltender Tommy Salo from the slot on the only
shot in overtime.
</P>
<P>
	   Garry Valk and Igor Korolev scored in the third period for Toronto.
</P>
<P>
	   Todd Marchant and Ryan Smyth scored in the second period for the Oilers.
</P>
<P>
	   Marchant opened the scoring at 5:01 of the second by racing to the edge of
the crease to take a pass from Mike Grier from along the left boards and scpre.
</P>
<P>
	   Smyth set a screen in front of goalie Curtis Joseph and Tom Poti's shot from
the point deflected off him on a power play at 15:17.
</P>
<P>
	   Valk scored on a backhander from the slot that just slid over the goal-line
at 2:29 of the third.
</P>
<P>
	   Korolev tied the game with a deflection from close range, off a perfect pass
from Dmitri Khristich, at 5:37 of the third.
</P>
<P>
	   Toronto's Tie Domi left late in the first period after jamming the butt end
of his stick in his chest during play along the end boards. He didn't return.
</P>
<P>
	   Wendel Clark played his first game since rejoining the Leafs. He had a minor
penalty for roughing following an exchange with Sean Brown at 6:01 of the first.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
