<DATE_TIME> 2000-01-15 00:59 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> SuperSonics 91, Spurs 85  </HEADLINE>
    By JIM COUR AP Sports Writer
<TEXT>
<P>
	   SEATTLE (AP) -- Gary Payton scored 25 points and Vin Baker added 23 as the
Seattle SuperSonics won their fourth straight game by beating the San Antonio
Spurs 91-85 Friday night.
</P>
<P>
	   The Spurs, led by Tim Duncan's 32 points and 16 rebounds, lost for the
second night in a row. They were beaten on Thursday night in Sacramento.
</P>
<P>
	   The Sonics never trailed after grabbing an 18-2 lead in the first 5:20, but
the defending NBA champions got within one point at 60-59 in the third quarter.
</P>
<P>
	   Seattle beat San Antonio for the second time this season.
</P>
<P>
	   The Sonics finished the game without their best big man, Baker, who fouled
out with 2:34 to go with his team ahead 87-81.
</P>
<P>
	   San Antonio got 20 points from David Robinson.
</P>
<P>
	   Ruben Patterson had 15 points and Brent Barry 12 for Seattle. Horace Grant
and Baker each had nine rebounds.
</P>
<P>
	   In the fourth quarter, Robinson cut Seattle's lead to 83-79 with a
17-footer, but Baker answered with two free throws after being fouled by Samaki
Walker.
</P>
<P>
	   After the Spurs' Antonio Daniels threw the ball out of bounds, Barry scored
on a fastbreak dunk after a steal by Terry Porter.
</P>
<P>
	   Avery Johnson made another critical San Antonio turnover when he dribbled
the ball out of bounds with 2:34 left and the Sonics ahead 87-81.
</P>
<P>
	   Duncan scored 14 points in the third quarter when the Spurs crept to 60-59
with 6:04 gone in the period. The Sonics came back to take a 73-63 lead on a
free throw by Baker before San Antonio got the last six points of the quarter,
four on a pair of baskets by Duncan.
</P>
<P>
	   The Sonics led 49-42 at halftime after going ahead by 21 in the opening
quarter when they scored 18 unanswered points after Robinson opened the game
with a 15-footer. In that 18-0 run, Barry and Payton each hit 3-pointers.
</P>
<P>
	   Jaren Jackson of San Antonio sank a 3-pointer, but Payton hit consecutive
3-pointers to give Seattle a 24-5 advantage with 7:06 gone in the game.
</P>
<P>
	   But the Spurs came back in the second period and cut Seattle's lead to five
at 41-36 on two free throws by Duncan with 3:12 left in the first half.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
