<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-01-15 03:11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ticket Refund Set for Phills Delays  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    CHARLOTTE, N.C. (AP) -- The Charlotte Hornets on Friday announced a ticket
refund policy for the two home games postponed because of the death of
co-captain Bobby Phills.
</P>
<P>
	   In addition to offering refunds at the point of purchase, the Hornets said
tickets could be exchanged for future games at the Charlotte Coliseum.
</P>
<P>
	   Tickets could either be used for the identical seats at the two rescheduled
games, or they could be exchanged for tickets to another game this season.
</P>
<P>
	   The NBA postponed Wednesday night's game against Chicago after Phills was
killed earlier in the day.
</P>
<P>
	   Police said Phills and teammate David Wesley were racing late Wednesday
morning after the team's morning shootaround. The two were traveling at speeds
in excess of 75 mph when Phills lost control of his car in a 45-mph zone and
slid into oncoming traffic. His car was struck in the driver's side door by an
oncoming sedan. Phills was pronounced dead at the scene.
</P>
<P>
	   The league also postponed Friday night's game against New York, which had
been scheduled to start just a few hours after a memorial service for Phills.
</P>
<P>
	   League officials said Friday that both games would be rescheduled, but that
the makeup dates had yet to be determined.
</P>
<P>
	   The two teams will play tonight at New York. After the game, the team was to
take a charter back to Charlotte, then fly to Baton Rouge on Sunday for Phills'
funeral and burial.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
