<HEADLINE> Councilman Apologizes for Insult  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SUFFOLK, Va. (AP) -- A city councilman apologized after his muttered insult
of a citizen was picked up by a cable television microphone.
</P>
<P>
	   Councilman Curtis R. Milteer said he went to the home of T.C. Williams to
deliver the apology after he learned his unflattering characterization of
Williams had been broadcast.
</P>
<P>
	   It was during a Jan. 5 council meeting that Williams, a neighborhood
activist, criticized a plan to spend $2 million on a police precinct.
</P>
<P>
	   ``If you've got two million bucks and you don't know what to do with it,
call me,'' Williams told the panel.
</P>
<P>
	   On the cable broadcast, Milteer was then heard to mutter, ``Damn nut.''
</P>
<P>
	   Milteer said Friday he intends to apologize again -- this time publicly --
at a meeting next week.
</P>
<P>
	   ``It was an error of the head and not the heart,'' Milteer said.
</P>
<P>
	   Williams accepted Milteer's regrets, but said he thinks the public apology
is necessary.
</P>
</TEXT>
