<HEADLINE> Murder Suspect Turned Over to Mexico  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MEXICO CITY (AP) -- A man charged with murder has been extradited from the
United States to face charges in Mexico, the federal attorney general's office
said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
	   Francisco Munoz Mendez, who is charged with killing his uncle during an
October 1997 argument in Jalisco state, was turned over to Mexican authorities
on Friday, according to a statement from the office.
</P>
<P>
	   Acting on a request from Mexico, U.S. authorities captured Munoz in Moreno
Valley, Calif., on Dec. 9. A U.S. district court approved Mexico's request for
extradition on Dec. 17.
</P>
