<DATE_TIME> 2000-01-15 19:44 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italian Protest Ended With Teargas  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ROME (AP) -- Police threw tear gas and charged on horseback Saturday to break
up a tumultuous protest outside a Rome detention center for illegal immigrants.
The clash left protesters and police with minor injuries.
</P>
<P>
	   A crowd that at times grew to 500 clashed with police off and on throughout
the day near the Ponte Galeria center on Rome's outskirts, demanding they be
allowed to inspect conditions inside the center.
</P>
<P>
	   Protesters threw rocks at police and hid behind hastily erected street
barricades. Police fired tear gas and clubbed the crowd, sometimes charging it
on horseback.
</P>
<P>
	   The fracas left a few on both sides bleeding, including one protester who
was taken away by ambulance with what appeared to be a minor injury.
</P>
<P>
	   Italy keeps immigrants caught without proper visas in detention centers for
up to 30 days. Most are then ordered expelled.
</P>
<P>
	   Conditions at the centers attracted increased attention after three
Tunisians died Dec. 29 in a fire they had set to try to cover their escape from
a center in Sicily.
</P>
</TEXT>
