<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-01-15 23:17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Clinton Extends Cuban Lawsuits Bar  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- President Clinton has extended for six more months a ban
on U.S. companies suing companies that deal in properties seized after Fidel
Castro took power in Cuba, the White House said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
	   A statement from the press office said Clinton notified Congress on Friday
that he was taking the action ``in the natural interest and because it is the
best way to secure the ... objective of promoting a transition to democracy in
Cuba.''
</P>
<P>
	   Clinton has regularly used his authority to suspend the right of U.S.
companies to sue under the 1996 Helms-Burton Act in an effort to avoid angering
European countries and Canada.
</P>
<P>
	   A number of companies headquartered in Canada and Europe do business with
Cuba and have been critical of the Helms-Burton law.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-01-15-00 2317 </TRAILER>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> APW20000115.0228 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-01-15 23:23 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jazz 112, Clippers 75  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    SALT LAKE CITY (AP) -- Karl Malone scored 24 points as Utah beat the Los
Angeles Clippers 112-75 on Saturday night, giving Jazz coach Jerry Sloan his
700th career coaching victory.
</P>
<P>
	   Sloan, 700-403 as a head coach with Chicago and Utah, is the 12th coach in
NBA history to reach the milestone. His first victory as coach of the Jazz was
against the Clippers in 1988.
</P>
<P>
	   Bryon Russell and Jeff Hornacek each added 17 to help the Jazz win for the
eighth time in nine games.
</P>
<P>
	   Derek Anderson and Michael Olowokandi each scored 18 points for Los Angeles.
The Clippers have seven straight on the road, and four in a row overall. They
are 0-17 in the Delta Center.
</P>
<P>
	   Utah, which trailed early in the second period, outscored the Clippers 18-3
to take a 12-point halftime lead. The Clippers would come no closer than 66-58
midway through the third period as Utah won for the 16th time in its last 19
games.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-01-15-00 2323 </TRAILER>
